cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with executing manipulation skills on a robot. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper assumes that point clouds of the objects can be obtained, which requires computer vision techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the system must interpret the point clouds and decide how to use the tool to complete a manipulation task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the system encodes manipulation skills in a generic way with parameters that can be filled in at run-time via queries to a robot perception module. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with everyday manipulations that humans commonly perform.
